description.plain:
Khalil Tatem (born 19 August 1997), better known by his stage name KILLY, is a rapper from Toronto, Canada whose melodic, dark, ambient, trap sound is inspired by fellow rapper Travis Scott.

KILLY first saw major popularity with his song “Killamonjaro,” which reached nearly 15 million views on YouTube in a year. He released his debut studio album, Surrender Your Soul, in March 2018, and the five-song KILLSTREAK EP in September.

description.plain:
After it generated a strong buzz on Soundcloud, KILLY dropped the official video for “Killamonjaro” in February 2017, before finally releasing the track on his debut mixtape Surrender Your Soul a year later in March 2018.

Rapping over an eerie piano and bass-driven beat from newcomer Gray Jacques, KILLY seeks to capture the feeling of being high on Molly, weed, lean and xanax, leading to a spacey and ethereal vibe.

Imagined as a blood-sucking creature that is usually the size of a small bear, Killy compares himself to the ancient beast, stating that his rarity and success has garnered him an exclusive status. The track sees Killy rapping about a number of topics, ranging from the women in his life, his wealth and his hometown of Toronto, Ontario.

“Starstream*” is the fourth track off of Killy’s 2017 LP “Surrender Your Soul”.

“Starstream*” is characterized by melancholy. The songs two producers, Binns and Hypontic Beatz, used a trickling synth, distorted bass and stuttering effects to create a dream-like atmosphere. This, combined with Killy’s cadence, creates a tone of loving the present he’s in, but struggling with issues that have arisen from his notoriety.

description.plain:
“Sailor Moon” also known as “Lean on Me” is Killy’s second most highly anticipated snippet to be released in 2019, the first being “Déjà Vu”.

While Killy was getting ready to release his album LIGHT PATH 8, he would post on his social media a snippet to his song “Sailor Moon” on May 28, 2019. The snippet would accumulate over 10K views on his Instagram, but it would later get deleted. In the description of the snippet video, Killy wrote:

Wasn’t gonna drop this but I’m bored in my hotel album coming soon!!!

The track was predicted to be on Killy’s album LIGHT PATH 8, but it wasn’t on the tracklist. Killy could be planning to release the song as a single.
